XML_CASESUMMARY.SUMMARY:
The crash occurred in the eastbound lanes of a four-lane interstate roadway divided by a grass and gravel median. There were rumble strips on each shoulder. There were two lanes in each direction. The roadway was asphalt with a posted speed limit of 113 kph (70 mph). The roadway was dry and slightly curved to the right (radius of curvature of 882 meters) and with an 8% super-elevation. The crash occurred about mid-morning on a dry clear weekend day. Traffic was light.
V1, a 1997 Toyota Corolla, 4-door with 4 occupants, was traveling eastbound on lane two. V1 was negotiating the slightly right curved road when it drove off the left edge of the roadway onto the rumble strip and then the grass median. The noise startled the driver who began to steer right while braking. The driver overcompensated causing the car to spin around clockwise. It re-entered the roadway and traveled across the two eastbound lanes. V1 went off the right side of the roadway across the shoulder onto a soft stretch of roadside. V1 flipped over onto its right side and then 3 more quarter turns before it struck an embankment, landing upright, headed north with the rear end resting on the embankment which had a slope of about 16%. The distance traveled by V1 during rollover was approximately 14 meters.
A 31-year old male drove V1. No one in the vehicle was injured because all were belted in. There were two children in child seats in the back seat of the vehicle. According to the owner of the vehicle, who was seated in the right front passenger seat, driver had been drinking beer earlier that morning. There was an open 12 pack of beer on the right front floorboard. She said she had tried to get him to let her drive but he refused. The driver was in route to visit a relative nearby and was talking to him on the cell phone.
The Critical Pre-crash Event for V1 was this vehicle traveling off the right edge of the roadway. The Critical Reason for the Critical Event was overcompensation. Associated factors included driving although he had been drinking alcohol, inadequate or inappropriate evasive action with respect to achieving crash avoidance; being upset by work and family related stress, in an unfamiliar vehicle, on an unfamiliar roadway, all the while being distracted while talking on a cell phone.
